Edition:
Quote:  Whatever were the ancient-English meanings in Otago [a `hundred'] came [in 1850s-60s] to signify run country surveyed and cut up for small settlement freeholds. And one can appreciate what the term meant to a runholder who had just got stocked up and his run working efficiently.
